# Snapshot: code/int_bool_type_errors

## Case 01

### Source: `test/tmp_fs/code.frog`

```frog
true 5 + print
```

### Run and Build

Commands:

```text
py -m frog run test/tmp_fs/code.frog
py -m frog -l WARN build -r test/tmp_fs/code.frog
```

Output:

```text
[ERROR] test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:8: stack doesnt match at 0 for IntrinsicType.ADD: expected INT() but got BOOL()
[NOTE] stack:
      0. BOOL()@test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:1
      1. INT()@test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:6
[NOTE] ins:
      0. INT()
      1. INT()
[EXIT CODE] 1
```

